  "title": "Business Analyst (Java, JavaScript, SQL, AWS Cloud)",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a <strong>Business Analyst</strong> who can work closely with stakeholders to analyze business needs and translate them into end-to-end, practical technology solutions. The role requires a strong balance of business analysis, technical comprehension, and communication skills.</p><p><strong>Key Mandatory Competencies</strong></p><ol><li>Possesses foundational knowledge of<u> Java, JavaScript, SQL, and AWS Cloud</u></li><li>Strong Business Analysis & Ownership: Able to independently manage assigned BA tasks, collaborate with cross-functional stakeholders, and piece together fragmented requirements into holistic, well-structured solutions for business problems.</li><li>Clear & Confident Communication: Demonstrates the ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear, non-technical language for clients and business users, supporting workshops, discussions, and client communications.</li></ol><p><strong>Role Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with senior consultants and stakeholders to gather, analyze, and clarify business and technical requirements.</li><li>Translate business needs into functional and technical specifications, workflows, and solution designs.</li><li>Support solution development through data analysis, documentation, and requirement validation.</li><li>Contribute to stakeholder workshops, presentations, and project communications, ensuring clarity and alignment across technical and non-technical audiences.</li></ul><p><strong>Nice-to-Have Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with event-driven architecture (Kafka), legacy system migration, client-facing workshops, SDLC knowledge, and strong documentation or problem-decomposition skills will be advantageous but are not mandatory.</li></ul>",
